WEBVTT

00:03.771 --> 00:06.907
My neighbor Kenny and his
girlfriend go all the time.

00:06.974 --> 00:09.110
The rides were actually fun,
Claire,

00:09.177 --> 00:11.412
even though they hurl you
through the air very quickly

00:11.479 --> 00:13.914
without a proper
three-point seat belt.

00:13.981 --> 00:16.384
It was worth
the $300 I spent.

00:16.450 --> 00:18.086
What kind of carnival
will cost you that
much money?

00:18.152 --> 00:20.388
It was not
just the carnival.

00:20.454 --> 00:23.391
Kenny's girlfriend wanted to
go to see a movie afterwards,

00:23.457 --> 00:25.393
but I just got
the second edition

00:25.459 --> 00:27.528
of Chaikof's
Atlas of Vascular Therapy

00:27.595 --> 00:29.063
so decided not to go.

00:29.130 --> 00:30.164
And you paid
for everyone?

00:30.231 --> 00:31.532
I had to.
I lost the bet.

00:31.599 --> 00:34.235
Rounds will have to wait.
We have a consult come up.

00:34.302 --> 00:35.703
Hunter Denoble, 38.

00:35.769 --> 00:38.072
Came into the E.R.
this morning complaining
of severe neck pain.

00:38.139 --> 00:40.007
X-rays
show anterolisthesis.

00:40.074 --> 00:42.243
A herniated disc.
Thirty-eight a little young
for that, isn't it?

00:42.310 --> 00:44.812
Unless there's a history
of spinal trauma.

00:44.878 --> 00:46.114
There is.

00:46.180 --> 00:48.316
Hunter fractured
seven vertebrae
in his neck and back

00:48.382 --> 00:50.151
in a motorcycle accident
10 years ago.

00:50.218 --> 00:51.752
He was one of
my first patients.

00:51.819 --> 00:54.355
Suffered complete paralysis
from the chest down.

00:54.422 --> 00:56.957
...a few months back,
just gnawing pain.

00:57.024 --> 00:58.992
Ibuprofen usually
took the edge off.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.594
Every day?

01:00.661 --> 01:03.497
Uh, yeah, give or take.

01:03.564 --> 01:06.100
It's not that bad.
Last night
things changed.

01:06.167 --> 01:07.268
He couldn't move
his neck at all,

01:07.335 --> 01:09.337
and the pain medicine
had no effect.

01:09.403 --> 01:12.373
So, he wanted to tough it out,
but I dragged him in here.

01:12.440 --> 01:13.674
Yeah, it sounds like you.

01:13.741 --> 01:14.942
(HUNTER CHUCKLES)
Feel that?

01:15.008 --> 01:16.009
Yeah.

01:16.076 --> 01:17.311
And that?
Mmm-hmm.

01:17.378 --> 01:19.113
I made partner
at the firm.

01:19.180 --> 01:21.249
I don't like
to call in sick.

01:21.315 --> 01:25.153
And let's face it, I've spent
enough nights in hospital
rooms for five lifetimes.

01:25.219 --> 01:27.355
Can't argue with that.
Squeeze my hands.

01:30.057 --> 01:32.393
You have any tingling
or weakness in your arms?

01:32.460 --> 01:33.961
No.

01:34.027 --> 01:36.797
The plain films showed
what looked like
a herniated disc.

01:36.864 --> 01:39.400
Which would mean...?

01:39.467 --> 01:41.202
Artificial
disc replacement.

01:41.269 --> 01:45.105
Day procedure, he'd be out
by the morning at the latest.

01:45.173 --> 01:47.175
You married him?

01:49.643 --> 01:52.480
Yes, three years ago
in Cancun.
It was lovely.

01:52.546 --> 01:55.149
Even though
he's in a wheelchair?

01:55.216 --> 01:56.417
Shaun.
HUNTER: Oh, no worries.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.486
I get this all the time.

01:58.552 --> 02:00.521
Sure,
she can never wear heels,
but think of the parking.

02:00.588 --> 02:02.055
(CHUCKLES)

02:02.122 --> 02:03.957
(GROANS, INHALES SHARPLY)
DR. MELENDEZ:
What happened?

02:04.024 --> 02:06.059
Pain shot right down
through my legs.

02:06.126 --> 02:08.128
Your legs?
Yeah.

02:08.196 --> 02:10.364
I haven't felt anything
below my chest in 10 years.

02:10.431 --> 02:11.799
What the hell is going on?

02:12.400 --> 02:14.268
**

02:14.335 --> 02:16.337
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

02:25.413 --> 02:29.049
* When I saw the break of day

02:29.116 --> 02:33.086
* I wished that
I could fly away

02:33.153 --> 02:36.824
* Instead of kneeling
in the sand

02:36.890 --> 02:41.929
* Catching teardrops
in my hand

02:41.995 --> 02:48.936
* My heart is drenched in wine

02:49.002 --> 02:54.942
* But you'll be on my mind

02:55.008 --> 02:58.078
* Forever *

02:58.145 --> 02:59.146
Mom.

03:00.080 --> 03:01.114
(GASPS)

03:01.181 --> 03:02.983
Well, there's my girl.

03:07.087 --> 03:08.456
CLAIRE: I don't
want to see you.

03:08.522 --> 03:10.324
But I haven't
seen you in years.

03:10.391 --> 03:11.959
Don't run away from me.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.094
Can we talk?
Since I don't
want to see you,

03:14.161 --> 03:16.464
it follows that I don't want
to hear from you, either.

03:18.666 --> 03:20.334
I just came in
to get antibiotics.

03:20.401 --> 03:22.135
My surgeon doesn't work
on Fridays.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.204
It feels fine.

03:24.272 --> 03:26.073
Sorry, it's not fine.

03:26.139 --> 03:28.108
This implant
is definitely infected.

03:28.175 --> 03:29.943
Just that one, though,
right?

03:30.010 --> 03:31.512
Yes. At this point,

03:31.579 --> 03:35.115
your butt lift, tummy tuck,
lipo, and breast augmentation

03:35.182 --> 03:37.318
appear to be healthy.

03:38.986 --> 03:40.888
But I need to remove
this one and clean the area

03:40.954 --> 03:41.989
before
the bacteria spreads.

03:42.055 --> 03:43.791
Well,
can you replace it?

03:43.857 --> 03:45.459
Once the infection
is resolved

03:45.526 --> 03:47.027
and you have
a few months to heal.

03:47.094 --> 03:49.830
I don't want to walk
around with half
of a face for a few months.

03:49.897 --> 03:51.999
Isn't there anything
you can do
to save the implant?

03:52.065 --> 03:53.934
I can't make
any guarantees,

03:54.001 --> 03:56.570
but if I can replace
the implant without
risking re-infection, I will.

03:58.539 --> 04:00.173
Okay, Doctor.

04:09.383 --> 04:13.020
I didn't understand
the lyrics, but I liked
your mom's voice.

04:13.954 --> 04:16.724
Is she
a professional singer?

04:16.790 --> 04:19.827
She is a lot of things.

04:19.893 --> 04:21.729
Great mom
wasn't one of them.

04:21.795 --> 04:23.464
How so?

04:23.531 --> 04:26.634
A lot of people have
issues with their parents,
nothing new.

04:26.700 --> 04:29.069
But everyone's story's
different.

04:31.705 --> 04:33.273
How so?

04:36.944 --> 04:38.346
When I was in high school,

04:38.412 --> 04:41.148
I babysat the kids
in my neighborhood.

04:41.214 --> 04:42.916
I wanted to buy
a laptop for school

04:42.983 --> 04:45.152
like a lot of my friends had,

04:45.218 --> 04:48.356
so I saved up 1,000 bucks.

04:48.956 --> 04:50.223
I came home one day,

04:50.290 --> 04:53.361
and the money was gone
and so was my mother.

04:53.427 --> 04:56.397
And three days later,

04:56.464 --> 04:58.832
she came back from Reno

04:58.899 --> 05:03.236
with a designer dress
and a guy named Ricky.

05:05.238 --> 05:07.240
I never got the laptop.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.677
**

05:13.614 --> 05:15.883
My mom made pancakes.

05:15.949 --> 05:17.217
They were good.

05:17.284 --> 05:19.487
(CHUCKLES)

05:19.553 --> 05:21.088
Mmm, what is that?

05:26.226 --> 05:28.095
I've never seen
anything like that.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.897
Maybe
a spinal column tumor.

05:29.963 --> 05:32.566
Hunter's initial
spinal cord injury

05:32.633 --> 05:36.404
from the motorcycle accident
that caused his paralysis
was at T1,

05:36.470 --> 05:39.106
but that part looks
almost completely normal now.

05:40.040 --> 05:44.044
Hunter's phantom pain
is real.

05:48.015 --> 05:49.983
My former mentor, Sonya Kung,

05:50.050 --> 05:51.885
is head of the surgical
residency program

05:51.952 --> 05:53.454
at Denver
Memorial Hospital.

05:53.521 --> 05:55.322
If you want a meeting,
I'll make the call.

05:56.524 --> 05:58.125
Why?

05:58.191 --> 06:00.027
You're gonna need a job
after this year.

06:01.161 --> 06:02.663
You just trying to
screw with my head,

06:02.730 --> 06:03.997
or are you actually
being serious?

06:04.064 --> 06:05.566
The opportunity is real.

06:05.633 --> 06:07.901
I'm trying to be nice.

06:07.968 --> 06:10.203
I do that
when it doesn't hurt me.

06:10.270 --> 06:11.939
And this definitely
doesn't hurt you,

06:12.005 --> 06:14.374
you getting rid of
some competition.

06:14.442 --> 06:18.378
True, although you're not high
on my list of threats.

06:18.446 --> 06:20.581
This would be a much bigger
benefit for you.

06:20.648 --> 06:23.617
Look, I fought to stay here.

06:23.684 --> 06:25.252
I'm not going anywhere.

06:25.318 --> 06:28.489
**

06:32.325 --> 06:34.795
It's very rare,
but after many years

06:34.862 --> 06:37.164
with a bruised cord like yours
that isn't severed,

06:37.230 --> 06:39.232
it can start to
function again.

06:39.299 --> 06:41.869
So, this mass
is causing Hunter's pain?

06:41.935 --> 06:43.170
Yes.

06:43.236 --> 06:44.271
If the cord is healthy,

06:44.337 --> 06:46.273
why aren't I feeling
more than pain?

06:46.339 --> 06:48.041
The mass is compressing
the healthy cord,

06:48.108 --> 06:49.477
just letting the pain
through.

06:49.543 --> 06:51.178
We still have to do

06:51.244 --> 06:53.981
some more advanced imaging
to map the mass,

06:54.047 --> 06:55.616
but I am fairly confident

06:55.683 --> 06:57.250
that if we removed it
that could change.

06:59.853 --> 07:01.555
You may be able
to walk again.

07:02.222 --> 07:05.759
**

07:11.499 --> 07:12.766
We were able to
clean out the infection

07:12.833 --> 07:15.202
and swap in a new implant.
I am very pleased.

07:15.268 --> 07:16.537
You think it looks okay?

07:16.604 --> 07:20.140
I love it,
and you are going to
look great at the beach.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.344
Wailea?

07:24.411 --> 07:25.679
(CHUCKLES)

07:25.746 --> 07:27.681
We went there
on our honeymoon.

07:27.748 --> 07:29.449
Thank you. (LAUGHS)

07:29.517 --> 07:30.784
Ooh.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.653
He's taking you to Hawaii.
You should be hugging him.

07:32.720 --> 07:35.088
Oh, I'm so relieved.

07:36.857 --> 07:38.559
Satisfied customers.

07:38.626 --> 07:41.995
This is why cosmetics
is the most fun specialty.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.531
Now, we're gonna
monitor you closely.

07:43.597 --> 07:46.667
There is a risk
the infection could have
seeded to other implants.

07:46.734 --> 07:48.101
Keep me posted.

07:48.168 --> 07:49.236
Yes, Chief.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.871
I'll take the early shift.

07:53.473 --> 07:58.178
Once I'm on my feet,
I'm never sitting down again.

07:58.245 --> 08:00.814
I'm gonna
take Cora dancing.

08:00.881 --> 08:02.583
She's a great dancer.

08:02.650 --> 08:04.351
Oh, no.

08:04.417 --> 08:05.853
I push myself.

08:05.919 --> 08:08.421
No offense. It's my rule.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.558
(WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON PA)

08:10.624 --> 08:12.125
Right.

08:13.460 --> 08:14.695
If this works,

08:14.762 --> 08:17.197
after a considerable amount
of physical therapy

08:17.264 --> 08:18.932
you may be able to walk,

08:18.999 --> 08:21.434
but that doesn't mean
you'll be a very good dancer.

08:21.501 --> 08:23.837
After years of atrophy
from not moving your legs,

08:23.904 --> 08:25.372
you will likely be
very bad.

08:25.438 --> 08:26.940
(CHUCKLES)

08:29.577 --> 08:31.679
You know what
the worst part is?

08:31.745 --> 08:33.146
It isn't
being in the chair.

08:33.213 --> 08:35.583
It's that people
see the chair first.

08:35.649 --> 08:37.050
They don't see me.

08:37.117 --> 08:38.518
You know what
I'm talking about.

08:38.586 --> 08:41.589
Why would I know
what you're talking about?

08:41.655 --> 08:44.524
My brother-in-law's
on the spectrum.
So's my assistant.

08:44.592 --> 08:47.394
I make it a priority of hiring
people with disabilities.

08:47.460 --> 08:49.062
Let me guess.
When you first
started working here,

08:49.129 --> 08:51.398
no one believed in you.
They didn't know me.

08:51.464 --> 08:53.901
They didn't know that I was
going to make a good surgeon.

08:53.967 --> 08:55.302
HUNTER: No.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.406
You were different.

08:59.472 --> 09:00.974
I guarantee you
every other doctor

09:01.041 --> 09:03.110
started with a basic
level of respect.

09:03.176 --> 09:05.646
It's implied
they're competent.

09:07.414 --> 09:09.950
We waste our time
and energy trying
to prove that we belong.

09:11.384 --> 09:15.155
**

09:19.226 --> 09:20.360
EMMA: I'm fine.

09:20.427 --> 09:22.295
She's just being thorough,
honey.

09:22.362 --> 09:24.632
You've been over my body
three times.

09:24.698 --> 09:26.499
Early infections
often mimic blemishes.

09:26.566 --> 09:27.901
It pays to be thorough.

09:29.637 --> 09:30.771
Is this sore?

09:30.838 --> 09:32.706
(BREATHES SHARPLY)
Maybe a little.

09:34.041 --> 09:35.042
What's wrong?

09:35.108 --> 09:36.476
It could be nothing,

09:36.543 --> 09:39.346
or it could be a carbuncle,
an early sign of infection.

09:39.412 --> 09:42.049
Dr. Andrews needs
to have a look at this.

09:48.055 --> 09:50.858
This varicocele is raising
testicular temperature

09:50.924 --> 09:53.026
and causing your sperm count
to be low.

09:53.093 --> 09:56.096
Surgically, I go in,
ligate the varicocele

09:56.163 --> 09:57.865
and re-check your numbers
in a few weeks.

09:57.931 --> 09:59.099
It's done under a local,

09:59.166 --> 10:02.135
so no anesthesia risks,
minimal blood loss.

10:02.202 --> 10:04.171
There's a risk of
low testosterone
and impotence,

10:04.237 --> 10:06.473
but recovery time's
usually a week at most.

10:10.543 --> 10:12.946
So, I could have kids,
I just might not be able
to make them?

10:13.013 --> 10:14.882
As I said,
it's low risk.

10:14.948 --> 10:16.950
I only mention it because
I'm obligated to inform you.

10:17.017 --> 10:19.687
Well, you're obligated to
inform me because it's a risk.

10:19.753 --> 10:22.690
It's an unlikely complication,
but, yes, it happens.

10:22.756 --> 10:24.124
It's outpatient.

10:24.191 --> 10:26.126
I do it right here
in the office.

10:26.193 --> 10:30.063
What I see here
is a chance to fix a problem.

10:30.130 --> 10:31.899
And I see a chance
to create a new one.

10:31.965 --> 10:34.735
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

10:34.802 --> 10:36.569
I'm... I'm sorry,
I have to go.
I have a patient.

10:37.771 --> 10:38.806
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:38.872 --> 10:39.873
(DOOR OPENS)

10:39.940 --> 10:41.574
Look, I see a lot of men
with this issue.

10:41.641 --> 10:43.711
Sure, they come in
because they want kids,

10:43.777 --> 10:46.413
but I think what
they really want is
to reaffirm themselves.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.148
And that's a good thing.

10:50.483 --> 10:51.484
Thank you.

10:54.654 --> 10:57.991
It's a spinal
arachnoid meningioma.

10:58.058 --> 10:59.860
Have you seen
one of these before?

10:59.927 --> 11:01.094
DR. MELENDEZ: Much smaller.

11:01.161 --> 11:02.730
They usually
don't get this big

11:02.796 --> 11:06.199
because the pain and weakness
brings the patient
into the E.R. fast.

11:06.266 --> 11:07.868
But in this case,
no pain,

11:07.935 --> 11:09.903
no E.R. visit
until it got this big.

11:09.970 --> 11:12.372
And it's wrapped around
the spinal cord tightly
and fused with the dura.

11:12.439 --> 11:14.908
Can we get a fiber-optic laser
and take it out in segments?

11:15.909 --> 11:18.611
No, I don't think so.

11:18.678 --> 11:22.482
It stopped growing
and settled in this position.

11:22.549 --> 11:25.853
But I do think
that we can dissect along
the subarachnoid plane

11:25.919 --> 11:27.554
down to the largest
segment at T2

11:27.620 --> 11:28.789
and remove it
in one piece.

11:28.856 --> 11:30.958
That's an extension
of the mass.

11:31.024 --> 11:33.794
Mmm, no.
It's the medullary pyramids.

11:33.861 --> 11:37.430
No.
It's an extension of the mass.

11:37.497 --> 11:41.668
The pyramids are more central
and the color is wrong.

11:42.369 --> 11:44.304
Murphy's right.

11:44.371 --> 11:47.207
The extension's
tightly adhered
to the brainstem.

11:50.043 --> 11:51.311
DR. ANDREWS: Who caught it?

11:51.378 --> 11:52.712
Jared did.

11:53.713 --> 11:54.982
DR. ANDREWS: Nice work.

11:55.048 --> 11:56.483
Most first-year residents
would have missed this.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.285
It's very small
on the surface,

11:58.351 --> 12:01.054
but I can feel the fluctuance
under the skin.

12:01.121 --> 12:02.890
What do we
need to do to fix it?

12:02.956 --> 12:04.224
(REMOVES GLOVES)

12:04.291 --> 12:06.526
We need to remove
all of the implants

12:06.593 --> 12:09.162
and some of the healthy
underlying tissue as well.

12:09.229 --> 12:12.599
Unfortunately, it will
cause significant
permanent scarring.

12:12.665 --> 12:14.935
No, no, no, you...
You can't do that.

12:15.002 --> 12:16.669
I'll look worse
than I did before.

12:16.736 --> 12:18.772
I... I don't get it.
You removed the bad
part from her face,

12:18.839 --> 12:21.441
and it's fixed.
Looks good,
no more infection.

12:21.508 --> 12:23.076
Let's just do the same
with the rest of 'em.

12:23.143 --> 12:24.644
It's not that simple.

12:24.711 --> 12:26.814
When we removed the infection
from Emma's cheek,

12:26.880 --> 12:29.783
it was under the pretense
it was a localized issue.

12:29.850 --> 12:32.285
If we just take out
the infection from
the new area,

12:32.352 --> 12:33.553
it could jump again.

12:35.789 --> 12:37.825
I won't do it.

12:37.891 --> 12:40.360
When an infection spreads,
it often moves very quickly.

12:40.427 --> 12:41.694
What Dr. Andrews
is saying...

12:41.761 --> 12:43.230
I understand
what he's saying.

12:45.198 --> 12:48.501
I'm 50 years old.

12:48.568 --> 12:51.905
When I went
to drop my daughter
off at Michigan,

12:51.972 --> 12:55.042
we went to that bar
on Liberty Street,

12:55.108 --> 12:56.810
where we first met.

12:56.877 --> 13:00.113
I saw myself sitting there
25 years ago,

13:00.180 --> 13:03.750
young, confident,
full of potential.

13:06.419 --> 13:07.754
Then you raise a kid

13:07.821 --> 13:11.658
and look after
your husband,

13:12.926 --> 13:14.127
a home.

13:18.298 --> 13:20.000
You lose touch
with who you were.

13:23.536 --> 13:25.772
You... You said it was
an infection, right?

13:25.839 --> 13:27.607
Like strep throat
or something.

13:28.575 --> 13:30.878
That's what
antibiotics are for.

13:30.944 --> 13:32.379
Couldn't we just
use that?

13:35.015 --> 13:39.086
We could try strong,
broad-spectrum antibiotics,

13:39.152 --> 13:41.221
but I really don't
want to do that.

13:41.288 --> 13:42.555
You could become septic.

13:42.622 --> 13:44.157
You could die.

13:44.224 --> 13:47.594
**

13:49.762 --> 13:51.564
It'll work.

13:52.265 --> 13:53.466
It has to.

13:56.836 --> 13:58.271
The brainstem is complex.

13:58.338 --> 14:00.840
Even our best imaging can't
provide a complete picture.

14:01.975 --> 14:04.377
So, then, you would just
leave the cyst in him?

14:04.444 --> 14:06.779
ALEX: Other than the pain,
it's not harming Hunter.

14:06.846 --> 14:08.115
It's stabilized now
and done growing.

14:08.181 --> 14:09.749
But what about
the pain?

14:09.816 --> 14:14.521
An implanted nerve inhibitor
will completely remove the
pain.

14:15.788 --> 14:17.490
But I won't
be able to walk.

14:19.259 --> 14:20.527
No.

14:25.298 --> 14:27.100
(SIGHS)

14:27.167 --> 14:29.736
Exactly how risky is removing
the mass from the brainstem?

14:29.802 --> 14:31.404
Everything that
keeps your heart beating

14:31.471 --> 14:33.140
and you breathing
is right there.

14:33.206 --> 14:35.909
The nerve inhibitor
is a day procedure.

14:35.976 --> 14:37.978
You'd sleep
in your bed tonight
pain-free.

14:38.045 --> 14:39.446
Give me a percentage
on this thing.

14:39.512 --> 14:40.981
Don't do this
to yourself.

14:41.048 --> 14:42.983
I don't like to give
those kinds of numbers.

14:43.050 --> 14:44.918
They're population-based,
and they don't apply to
your exact circumstance.

14:44.985 --> 14:46.286
I understand
how statistics work.

14:46.353 --> 14:48.488
But there's a number,
and it's relevant.

14:51.191 --> 14:54.561
There's a 15% chance
the surgery would kill you.

14:54.627 --> 14:56.896
**

15:02.402 --> 15:05.472
I remember
the moment I accepted
I'd never walk again.

15:07.107 --> 15:09.876
It wasn't when Dr. Melendez
told me after the accident.

15:11.578 --> 15:15.015
It was a few months later
when I was in rehab

15:15.082 --> 15:19.652
and I was trying to
get up in the standing frame.

15:19.719 --> 15:22.355
I looked out the window
and there's all these people
just living their lives.

15:24.857 --> 15:28.595
I'm trying to fix something
that I can't change,

15:28.661 --> 15:30.397
and life was going on
without me.

15:34.067 --> 15:36.203
So I started
living again.

15:39.906 --> 15:41.841
(SIGHS)

15:41.908 --> 15:43.443
But now there's
something I can do.

15:47.780 --> 15:49.149
Hunter...

15:52.919 --> 15:54.721
I want to talk
to Dr. Melendez.

15:59.392 --> 16:00.627
No.

16:00.693 --> 16:01.894
Please.

16:01.961 --> 16:04.064
(SIGHS)
Just go get Dr. Melendez.

16:04.998 --> 16:08.535
**

16:14.607 --> 16:16.943
(WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON PA)

16:18.811 --> 16:20.113
You curious?

16:21.714 --> 16:23.350
About why
I gave you the credit?

16:23.416 --> 16:25.252
I assume you thought
it was a set-up,

16:25.318 --> 16:28.088
that Andrews thought
you were wrong and you tried
to throw it on me.

16:28.155 --> 16:29.722
That's very cynical.

16:31.191 --> 16:33.760
The other alternative
is that you were being kind,

16:33.826 --> 16:35.428
which seems
very unlikely.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.630
There is
a third possibility.

16:39.132 --> 16:40.533
I'm proving a point.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.902
When you lose their respect,
no matter what you do,

16:42.969 --> 16:44.304
no matter how many wins
you chalk up,

16:44.371 --> 16:46.206
you'll never get it back.

16:46.273 --> 16:47.840
The game's already over.

16:47.907 --> 16:49.008
You lost.

16:50.777 --> 16:52.612
Does anyone like you?

16:52.679 --> 16:54.314
I like me.

16:54.381 --> 16:55.848
LAB TECH: I've got results.

16:56.349 --> 16:59.319
**

17:00.820 --> 17:03.056
I know this is her first cycle
of antibiotics,

17:03.123 --> 17:04.957
but I'm not seeing
any improvement.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.659
Her neutrophils
are through the roof.

17:07.494 --> 17:09.529
(PAPER RUSTLES)

17:09.596 --> 17:11.898
You'd be under anesthesia
for nine hours,

17:11.964 --> 17:14.534
and I'll need to make sure
that your body's healthy
enough to handle the stress.

17:14.601 --> 17:16.769
Will you tell him
not to do this, please?

17:18.004 --> 17:19.306
You don't care
what I think?

17:19.372 --> 17:20.773
HUNTER:
I'm the one in the chair.

17:20.840 --> 17:22.075
You have no idea
what that's like.

17:22.142 --> 17:24.077
I'm right there with you.

17:24.144 --> 17:25.745
Who carries you
up the stairs?

17:25.812 --> 17:27.547
Who pushes you out
through the sand

17:27.614 --> 17:29.149
so you can put your feet
in the water?

17:29.216 --> 17:31.084
Well, this way you
won't have to do
those things anymore.

17:31.151 --> 17:33.820
So you just want to gamble
the life that you have
for the life that you had?

17:33.886 --> 17:35.222
Cora.

17:37.324 --> 17:39.826
We have a great life,

17:39.892 --> 17:41.228
but I want to walk again.

17:42.362 --> 17:44.197
And I want you
to see me walk.

17:47.167 --> 17:49.102
I'm not gonna stand by
and watch you die.

17:49.169 --> 17:52.472
If you want to selfishly
gamble your life away,

17:52.539 --> 17:54.107
you're doing it
on your own.

17:56.676 --> 17:58.077
I'm doing this for us.

17:59.212 --> 18:01.748
No, you're doing this
for you.

18:03.250 --> 18:07.154
**

18:13.193 --> 18:14.561
She'll be back.

18:17.597 --> 18:19.566
(ELEVATOR CHIMES)

18:19.632 --> 18:21.801
WOMAN: (ON PA) Dr. Tolles
to Obstetrics, please.
Dr. Tolles to Obstetrics.

18:21.868 --> 18:23.536
Hey. Uh, I got a page?

18:29.309 --> 18:32.179
I'm busy, and I don't like
being tricked into coming
down here.

18:32.245 --> 18:34.214
Yeah, I know you hate me...
I don't hate you.

18:34.281 --> 18:36.048
Seeing you
is not healthy for me.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.252
Okay, wait...
Well, I just need to
tell you that I was sick.

18:43.022 --> 18:45.258
I am sick.

18:45.325 --> 18:46.893
I know, you've been telling me
that for years.

18:46.959 --> 18:48.428
You were right.

18:49.429 --> 18:51.063
I got help.

18:51.130 --> 18:53.333
They have me
on mood stabilizers.

18:53.400 --> 18:55.368
I'm doing better now.

18:55.435 --> 18:57.537
I mean, sometimes the meds
make me feel flat.

18:57.604 --> 19:00.173
You know, no highs, no fun.

19:00.240 --> 19:02.041
No lows, though, either.
It's worth it.

19:03.610 --> 19:06.246
I'd like to try again
to be your mom.

19:08.648 --> 19:11.451
I mean, maybe we could just
talk some more?

19:13.986 --> 19:15.822
I'll think about it.

19:15.888 --> 19:18.024
Well, take these.

19:18.090 --> 19:19.892
They need water
or they're gonna die.

19:21.428 --> 19:22.895
My number's on the card.

19:24.597 --> 19:28.635
**

19:35.275 --> 19:38.645
HUNTER: (PANTING)
I think I just won
the Tour de France.

19:38.711 --> 19:42.081
It's a long surgery.
It will put a lot of strain
on your heart.

19:42.148 --> 19:44.751
(GRUNTS)
(DEVICE BEEPS)

19:44.817 --> 19:48.020
Your cardiovascular fitness
is excellent.

19:49.389 --> 19:51.258
Huh!

19:51.324 --> 19:52.925
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

19:56.363 --> 19:57.730
You get it, right?

19:58.197 --> 19:59.866
Get what?

19:59.932 --> 20:01.501
Why I want this surgery
so bad.

20:02.935 --> 20:04.804
You'd jump at
a cure for autism,
wouldn't ya?

20:04.871 --> 20:07.907
There isn't
a cure for autism.

20:07.974 --> 20:11.844
Well, last week I didn't
think there was a surgery
to help me.

20:16.816 --> 20:19.486
The surgery isn't guaranteed
to help you walk.

20:20.387 --> 20:21.788
Why would you risk

20:21.854 --> 20:24.291
losing a person
who accepts you
the way you are?

20:24.357 --> 20:27.126
You may not
find another one.

20:27.193 --> 20:29.662
There are a lot of reasons
to marry me, you know?

20:31.163 --> 20:32.899
I'm sure there are a lot of
reasons to marry you.

20:32.965 --> 20:37.003
Yes. I'm organized,
I have excellent
visual-spatial memory,

20:37.069 --> 20:40.139
and Lea says I'm refreshingly
honest and fair.

20:40.206 --> 20:42.509
(CHUCKLES)

20:42.575 --> 20:46.513
I suppose Cora loves me
because I'm determined...

20:46.579 --> 20:48.348
I'm pretty smart,

20:49.982 --> 20:52.151
committed
to helping others,

20:52.218 --> 20:54.053
and most of all,
probably because I'm patient.

20:55.855 --> 20:57.890
Were you always
those things?

20:59.792 --> 21:02.228
Were you those things before
you were in the wheelchair?

21:05.732 --> 21:08.535
Your autism helped you.
That's your point.

21:08.601 --> 21:10.570
You're saying this chair
made me a better person.

21:13.340 --> 21:16.743
The difference is
losing this chair now

21:16.809 --> 21:19.812
won't make me lose
the lessons it gave me.

21:21.881 --> 21:24.617
**

21:27.787 --> 21:30.289
The antibiotics
aren't working.

21:30.357 --> 21:33.793
I told you if they didn't,
we'd be doing surgery next.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.764
No.

21:41.634 --> 21:43.235
She's going to die
if we don't act now.

21:46.205 --> 21:50.142
Honey, we need to
listen to the doctors.

21:52.379 --> 21:53.780
I need you to
trust me.

21:55.848 --> 21:59.786
I can't go back to being
like it used to be.

22:01.020 --> 22:02.288
You don't have a choice.

22:03.390 --> 22:06.493
**

22:09.996 --> 22:11.864
She wants
a second opinion.

22:11.931 --> 22:13.366
She's going to die.

22:13.433 --> 22:14.701
I told her that.

22:20.306 --> 22:23.042
**

22:32.051 --> 22:35.187
DR. MELENDEZ: Sometimes,
it's tough to actually get out
of those doors.

22:38.891 --> 22:40.192
(SIGHS)

22:41.327 --> 22:42.895
When I was a kid,

22:42.962 --> 22:46.298
my little sister
had an accident
climbing a tree,

22:46.365 --> 22:48.267
a traumatic brain injury,

22:48.334 --> 22:52.071
and I woke up every morning
dreaming that she was better,

22:53.706 --> 22:56.208
but she wasn't.

22:56.275 --> 22:57.744
I took care of her a lot.

22:57.810 --> 23:00.480
Brushed her teeth,
combed her hair, fed her.

23:04.083 --> 23:07.386
Hunter was my first patient
as an attending,

23:07.454 --> 23:09.956
and I had to walk
in that room
and tell him

23:10.022 --> 23:12.158
that there was nothing
I could do for him,

23:12.224 --> 23:14.326
nothing I could do
to fix him.

23:15.762 --> 23:17.296
And now there is?

23:20.399 --> 23:22.168
But there's no guarantee.

23:22.234 --> 23:23.836
There is never
a guarantee.

23:25.171 --> 23:27.674
(SIGHS)

23:32.211 --> 23:34.947
I'm sorry,
but I can't risk

23:35.014 --> 23:37.083
losing the man
that I fell in love with.

23:42.855 --> 23:46.358
You're not just afraid that
the surgery will kill him.

23:46.425 --> 23:47.960
You're afraid
that it might work.

23:50.129 --> 23:51.831
You've only known Hunter
in a wheelchair.

23:51.898 --> 23:55.267
Walking would be a fundamental
change in who he is,

23:56.703 --> 24:00.507
a fundamental change
in who you are as a couple.

24:00.573 --> 24:03.209
You're worried that
no matter what happens,
you're gonna lose him.

24:07.580 --> 24:09.048
Hunter seems to
have a great life.

24:09.115 --> 24:11.017
I don't know if I'd risk
giving that up.

24:11.083 --> 24:13.820
What if there was an operation
to make you a perfect doctor,

24:13.886 --> 24:18.357
never make a mistake,
but it had a, you know,
5% of killing you?

24:18.424 --> 24:19.626
Would you do it?

24:19.692 --> 24:21.360
That's not
a fair comparison.

24:21.427 --> 24:24.697
Well, you said Hunter's
doing fine the way he is,

24:24.764 --> 24:27.399
but we're talking about
giving him something more.

24:27.466 --> 24:28.868
What about 2%?

24:30.402 --> 24:31.738
I don't think
there's a number for me.

24:31.804 --> 24:33.339
Oh, of course
there's a number.

24:33.405 --> 24:35.041
Every time
you get in your car,

24:35.107 --> 24:36.275
hell, every time
you leave your home,

24:36.342 --> 24:37.844
you take a risk
something bad could happen.

24:37.910 --> 24:39.278
But you do it anyway,

24:39.345 --> 24:41.514
you know,
to make yourself better,

24:41.581 --> 24:43.415
to make the world better,

24:43.482 --> 24:44.551
sometimes just to have fun.

24:44.617 --> 24:47.219
Sometimes to go
to a carnival.

24:47.286 --> 24:49.021
Kenny's not your friend.

24:49.088 --> 24:50.422
He's using you.

24:51.591 --> 24:53.560
I...don't think so.

24:53.626 --> 24:54.761
We have fun.

24:54.827 --> 24:56.062
He's got a rap sheet.

24:56.128 --> 24:57.897
Mostly misdemeanors,

24:57.964 --> 25:00.567
but there's a couple
felony theft cases

25:00.633 --> 25:02.268
that were bargained down.

25:02.334 --> 25:05.672
Wait, you ran
a background check
on Kenny?

25:05.738 --> 25:08.941
Well, you start by talking,
I start by gathering evidence.

25:10.843 --> 25:12.845
I'll forward it to you.

25:12.912 --> 25:14.581
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

25:22.521 --> 25:25.592
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

25:27.226 --> 25:29.729
In my experience,
there are only two reasons

25:29.796 --> 25:32.164
why a married person has
this kind of cosmetic surgery.

25:32.231 --> 25:34.300
Either you're halfway
out the door or she is.

25:35.768 --> 25:37.136
Emma loves me.

25:38.638 --> 25:40.640
That's what I figured.

25:41.808 --> 25:43.943
The antibiotics
aren't working,

25:44.010 --> 25:46.445
so your wife is going to die

25:46.512 --> 25:48.280
unless you get in there
and you convince her

25:48.347 --> 25:50.316
that she doesn't need
any of this cosmetic surgery

25:50.382 --> 25:52.719
because you are a faithful,
loving husband.

26:01.661 --> 26:02.895
CORA: How's the pain?

26:07.033 --> 26:08.334
You know,
I think the adrenaline

26:08.400 --> 26:10.502
of actually doing this
is helping.

26:10.569 --> 26:12.071
It's the oxycodone.

26:13.840 --> 26:15.207
That's good.

26:16.375 --> 26:17.509
I'm glad you came back.

26:18.344 --> 26:19.979
I never left.

26:24.083 --> 26:25.417
(SIGHS)

26:28.420 --> 26:30.990
I don't want to do this
without you.

26:31.057 --> 26:32.892
I don't want to do anything
without you.

26:34.894 --> 26:36.996
If you can walk,

26:37.063 --> 26:38.564
you'll be different.

26:41.367 --> 26:44.003
You won't need me anymore.

26:44.070 --> 26:46.873
You think I married you
'cause I was having trouble
hanging clothes in my closet?

26:48.775 --> 26:50.109
You're my girl.

26:51.210 --> 26:53.112
I will always need you.

26:53.179 --> 26:55.715
Even if I could fly,

26:55.782 --> 26:58.584
who's gonna remind me to
call my mom on her birthday?

26:58.651 --> 27:00.119
Or to floss?
God, I hate flossing.

27:02.588 --> 27:04.590
Who's gonna remind me
to be a better person?

27:08.094 --> 27:10.029
Who's gonna hold my hand
when I'm scared?

27:11.563 --> 27:14.500
**

27:18.805 --> 27:20.506
That was nice.

27:21.640 --> 27:24.343
**

27:37.924 --> 27:39.625
You have to
have the surgery.

27:48.100 --> 27:52.404
You were distant before.

27:52.471 --> 27:55.374
Since the surgery,
you can't get enough of me.

27:56.608 --> 27:58.911
It worked.
You're happy, I'm happy.

27:58.978 --> 28:00.880
I love you.
I always have loved you.

28:00.947 --> 28:02.849
I always will.
You stopped loving me.

28:02.915 --> 28:04.483
No. Never.

28:04.550 --> 28:06.986
If you were in love with me,
you never would've
cheated on me.

28:08.454 --> 28:09.521
Barry,

28:12.191 --> 28:15.494
please, no more lies.

28:16.729 --> 28:19.131
You were never home.
We never talked.

28:19.932 --> 28:21.667
You were never there.

28:26.538 --> 28:28.140
There was never
another woman.

28:28.207 --> 28:31.878
I was gambling... A lot.

28:31.944 --> 28:34.146
I did it because I was ashamed
of the man that I'd become.

28:34.213 --> 28:36.048
When we got married,
I promised you the world,

28:36.115 --> 28:37.817
and instead I gave you
a mediocre life.

28:38.951 --> 28:43.589
When I was up,
it made me feel like a winner.

28:45.691 --> 28:49.295
And I was too embarrassed
to let you see me like that,
so I hid it from you.

28:49.361 --> 28:51.063
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

28:52.031 --> 28:56.235
**

28:59.972 --> 29:02.141
She's gonna do the surgery.

29:02.208 --> 29:03.309
Thank you.

29:05.144 --> 29:07.746
**

29:11.717 --> 29:13.786
Andrews needs an O.R.
for Emma Newton.

29:18.524 --> 29:22.261
**

29:34.073 --> 29:39.745
Claire, you're beautiful,
smart, and very good
at your job.

29:41.981 --> 29:44.450
Thank you, Shaun.
That's a very sweet thing
to say.

29:44.516 --> 29:48.220
Would you ever date someone
with a disability?

29:50.256 --> 29:51.623
Yeah, sure.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.994
(CHUCKLES)

29:55.061 --> 29:58.164
You could choose
the ideal mate,
Claire.

29:58.230 --> 30:01.333
Why would you want
the unnecessary burden?

30:01.400 --> 30:05.304
Everyone is dealing
with something.

30:05.371 --> 30:09.608
We just have to love
other people for who they are

30:10.676 --> 30:12.444
and hope they love us,
too.

30:15.147 --> 30:16.883
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

30:16.949 --> 30:18.617
O.R. 1's prepped for Hunter.

30:22.554 --> 30:24.356
I'll join you
in a minute.

30:24.423 --> 30:27.293
**

30:35.434 --> 30:37.236
(SIGHS)

30:45.411 --> 30:46.946
So, what changed her mind?

30:47.679 --> 30:48.714
Jared did.

30:52.418 --> 30:54.286
Morgan,
you're my first assist.

30:54.353 --> 30:56.655
**

31:01.527 --> 31:03.795
Make the call.

31:03.862 --> 31:05.797
Thanks.

31:05.864 --> 31:08.467
**

31:11.837 --> 31:13.572
(SIGHS)

31:13.639 --> 31:15.074
This is as far
as you can go.

31:15.141 --> 31:16.708
Nurse Matthews will take you
to the waiting room.

31:17.209 --> 31:18.477
Okay.

31:18.544 --> 31:20.980
Can I, uh...
Can I give him a kiss?

31:21.813 --> 31:23.449
Of course.

31:23.515 --> 31:27.286
**

31:34.193 --> 31:36.328
I can't do this.

31:36.395 --> 31:37.663
Yes, you can.

31:39.231 --> 31:41.333
This is what you do
in a relationship, right?

31:41.400 --> 31:43.635
You take chances,
together.

31:44.536 --> 31:46.638
(SNIFFLES)

31:48.340 --> 31:49.708
Okay.

31:49.775 --> 31:52.744
**

32:01.087 --> 32:04.090
(MONITOR BEEPING)
(RESPIRATOR HISSING)

32:07.293 --> 32:10.062
MORGAN: That's a large tissue
defect in the left breast.

32:10.129 --> 32:11.763
DR. ANDREWS: If we'd
been in here
six hours ago,

32:11.830 --> 32:14.066
I could have salvaged
more underlying muscle tissue.

32:14.133 --> 32:15.667
JARED: I'm noticing
her heart rate jump.

32:15.734 --> 32:16.902
You seeing that, JL?

32:18.204 --> 32:20.006
(BEEPING QUICKENS)
JL: I am now.

32:20.072 --> 32:21.507
DR. ANDREWS:
How's her surgical sites?

32:21.573 --> 32:23.042
I'm not seeing
any bleeding.

32:23.109 --> 32:24.210
Morgan,
what about your side?

32:24.276 --> 32:25.477
MORGAN: Everything
looks good here.

32:25.544 --> 32:26.912
Maybe
the anesthesia's light?

32:26.979 --> 32:29.648
JARED: Nope. No, something's
definitely happening.

32:29.715 --> 32:31.717
DR. ANDREWS: Jared's right.
(FLATLINING)

32:36.855 --> 32:38.024
DR. MELENDEZ: Suction, Claire.

32:38.090 --> 32:40.259
Give me a 25 on a 130.

32:40.326 --> 32:44.196
All right, Murphy,
I want you to cut
right under my forceps

32:44.263 --> 32:46.032
very carefully.

32:46.098 --> 32:49.368
(MONITOR BEEPING)

32:49.435 --> 32:50.702
SHAUN: Section's cut.

32:50.769 --> 32:52.404
DR. MELENDEZ: How are
the motor evoked potentials?

32:52.471 --> 32:54.740
ALEX: Signal's coming through,
spinal cord's
functioning normally.

32:59.711 --> 33:02.348
DR. MELENDEZ: The mass
has fully encased
the medullary cord.

33:05.951 --> 33:07.553
Give me
the ferromagnetic wand.

33:11.757 --> 33:14.560
I can't get the caudal end
clear of the underlying cord.

33:14.626 --> 33:16.295
(MONITOR BEEPING)
ALEX: Got a big
drop in potentials.

33:16.362 --> 33:17.696
SHAUN: We are compressing
his brainstem.

33:17.763 --> 33:18.930
DR. MELENDEZ:
What's his pressure?

33:18.997 --> 33:20.232
CLAIRE:
Mean arterial pressure's 70.

33:20.299 --> 33:21.633
ALEX: I got nothing now.

33:21.700 --> 33:23.535
DR. MELENDEZ: Push IV fluids.
Keep that MAP above 90.

33:23.602 --> 33:25.271
SHAUN: Hunter's going
into neurogenic shock.

33:25.337 --> 33:26.705
We need to
stop the surgery.

33:26.772 --> 33:27.973
DR. MELENDEZ:
I'm almost there.
20 seconds.

33:28.040 --> 33:30.076
CLAIRE: Pressure's 60.
Push vasopressors.

33:30.142 --> 33:32.111
DR. MELENDEZ:
The last piece is right there.

33:32.178 --> 33:34.213
It's probably edema.
Push 100 of dexamethasone.

33:36.615 --> 33:37.716
ALEX: Still nothing.

33:37.783 --> 33:38.984
SHAUN: He's dying.

33:39.051 --> 33:40.952
DR. MELENDEZ: It's one
damn centimeter of tissue.

33:42.688 --> 33:43.855
(FLATLINING)
(PADDLES WHINE)

33:43.922 --> 33:44.923
JARED: All clear.

33:44.990 --> 33:46.925
(PADDLES THUMP)

33:46.992 --> 33:49.328
MORGAN: That's her
second dose of amiodarone.
She's not responding.

33:49.395 --> 33:51.430
DR. ANDREWS:
She's thrown her
septic embolism.

33:51.497 --> 33:52.698
I'm cracking her chest.

33:52.764 --> 33:54.966
**

33:58.370 --> 33:59.771
(PADDLES WHINE)
JARED: Ten joules. Clear.

34:01.073 --> 34:02.574
DR. ANDREWS: Again.

34:02.641 --> 34:03.809
JARED: Clear.

34:06.011 --> 34:08.080
DR. ANDREWS: Starting
cardiac massage.

34:08.147 --> 34:10.482
(FLATLINE CONTINUES)

34:10.549 --> 34:13.719
**

34:26.332 --> 34:27.733
It's time to call it.

34:29.568 --> 34:31.670
(FLATLINE STOPS)

34:31.737 --> 34:33.739
MORGAN: Time of death, 10:23.

34:36.675 --> 34:39.845
**

